nrestored lacunae, and many emendations to thorny passages owed to physical damage in the manuscript as well as perhaps careless scribes and/or the poor quality of their model. The more authoritative version of the two texts is accompanied by fresh English translations and brief introductions, making both works widely accessible not just to Classicists but also to scholars and students of ancient medicine, ancient philosophy and Roman Imperial literary culture.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aDistress (Psychology)vEarly works to 1800. 0aMedicine, Greek and Roman. 4aEthik. 4aGalen. 4aMedizin. 4aRömisches Imperium.  aGalen.  aRoman Imperial Period.  aethics.  amedicine.1 aPolemis, Ioannis, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPolemis, Ioannis, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aXenophontos, Sophia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aXenophontos, Sophia, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2023 Part 1z97831111757820 cprintz978311132041040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783111320816zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783111320816zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783111320816/original  a978-3-11-117578-2 DG Plus DeG Package 2023 Part 1b2023  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA